      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Synthesized literature evidence for power-law hemolysis model applicability",
      "description": "A comprehensive synthesis of multiple prior studies spanning 2004–2021 examining the applicability of power-law hemolysis damage accumulation models (Giersiepen, Heuser-Opitz, Goubergrits variants) to centrifugal pump geometries. The synthesis aggregates regression coefficients, uncertainty bounds, and reported model errors from fourteen independent experimental campaigns and draws consolidated conclusions about model form adequacy for VAD operating envelopes. This node represents the aggregated epistemic foundation for the model-form credibility factor assessment and is treated as an established evidentiary basis for the current claim.",
      "prov:wasDerivedFrom": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-predicts-absolute-hemolysis-vad-cou2"
    },
