    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-credibility-review-board",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment package is accepted as a complete and compliant V&V 40 submission for regulatory review purposes. All 13 credibility factors have been addressed with documented rationale. Seven factors were formally assessed; six were identified as epistemic gaps consistent with MRL 5 requirements. The provenance chain linking the primary claim to experimental and computational evidence has been established. The literature synthesis node (vr-literature-synthesis-hemolysis-models) consolidates fourteen prior experimental campaigns and is treated as an established evidentiary foundation for model-form assessment. The overall credibility assessment outcome remains Not Accepted for the underlying device claim, but the assessment package itself is accepted as methodologically complete and suitable for submission.",
